{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🧑‍🍳 Neosantara AI Cookbook: Multimodal OCR\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/neosantara-xyz/examples/blob/main/cookbook/advanced/multimodal-ocr.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "This recipe demonstrates how to use multimodal (vision) models to perform Optical Character Recognition (OCR) and extract structured data from images using Neosantara AI."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install the OpenAI SDK\n",
    "!pip install openai\n",
    "\n",
    "# Setup API Key (for Google Colab)\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from google.colab import userdata\n",
    "    import os\n",
    "    os.environ[\"NEOSANTARA_API_KEY\"] = userdata.get('NEOSANTARA_API_KEY')\n",
    "    print(\"API Key loaded from Google Colab userdata.\")\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    import os\n",
    "    if \"NEOSANTARA_API_KEY\" in os.environ:\n",
    "        print(\"API Key loaded from environment variables.\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"Not running in Google Colab and NEOSANTARA_API_KEY not found in environment.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from openai import OpenAI\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "client = OpenAI(\n",
    "    api_key=os.getenv(\"NEOSANTARA_API_KEY\"),\n",
    "    base_url=\"https://api.neosantara.xyz/v1\"\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Basic Vision Processing\n",
    "\n",
    "In this section, we use the `glm-4.6` model to extract text from a receipt image."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "IMAGE_URL = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openai/openai-cookbook/main/examples/data/receipt.jpg\"\n",
    "\n",
    "response = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "    model=\"glm-4.6\",\n",
    "    messages=[
",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"user\",\n",
    "            \"content\": [\n",
    "                {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Describe the contents of this receipt in detail.\"},\n",
    "                {\n",
    "                    \"type\": \"image_url\",\n",
    "                    \"image_url\": {\n",
    "                        \"url\": IMAGE_URL\n",
    "                    }\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            ]\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(response.choices[0].message.content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Structured Output (JSON Mode)\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we'll extract the same data but in a structured JSON format, making it easy to process programmatically."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "response = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "    model=\"glm-4.6\",\n",
    "    messages=[
",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"user\",\n",
    "            \"content\": [\n",
    "                {\n",
    "                    \"type\": \"text\",\n",
    "                    \"text\": \"Extract the merchant name, date, items (with prices), and total amount from this receipt. Return the result in a JSON object.\"\n",
    "                },\n",
    "                {\n",
    "                    \"type\": \"image_url\",\n",
    "                    \"image_url\": {\n",
    "                        \"url\": IMAGE_URL\n",
    "                    }\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            ]\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    response_format={"type": "json_object"}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(response.choices[0].message.content)"
   ]
  }
 ],
